DESCRIPTION:Our friends from BloomAIR will conduct a 2-hour training cover
 ing three key topics:\n\n1. Know your rights when interacting with law enf
 orcement and federal agents\n\n2. How to identify ICE\n\n3. What to do if 
 you see or hear about a potential ICE sighting. \n\nThere will be time ava
 ilable for questions and answers as well. If you’re interested in organi
 zing directly against ICE if they come to our community\, or if you simply
  want to be prepared and empowered in the event of an ICE encounter\, don
 ’t miss this training.\n\nPlease arrive by 2:45pm so the training can be
 gin promptly at 3:00pm.\n\n### Photography and Video Policy\nISCI may take
  photos or videos at meetings and events to document\, share\, and promote
  our activities. When taking photos or videos\, ISCI representatives will 
 do their best to seek explicit consent before photographing individuals wi
 th their faces or names visible. We ask all participants taking personal p
 hotos or videos to seek consent as well and respect the wishes of those wh
 o do not want to be photographed or recorded. **Please note that in public
  settings\, including protests\, there is always the possibility of being 
 identifiably photographed.** Ultimately\, the responsibility for protectin
 g our identity lies with each of us individually. If you are concerned abo
 ut being photographed or recorded during Indivisible activities\, we stron
 gly encourage you to cover your face and other identifiable features.
